                  </hi> I live with my mother, at Wandsworth. On 26th Nov. I saw Hoare take a half-quartern loaf out of a baker's barrow—he ran a long way—I did not see what he did with it—Beazly was about three yards and a quarter away from him when he took the loaf—he walked down after him.</p>
